modules.description: Provides functions to interact with the r2pipe interface, including launching a radare2 instance, sending commands, and retrieving output as strings. Works with process handles, command strings, and raw output buffers. Used to automate reverse engineering tasks such as analyzing binary files and extracting disassembly.

Provides functions to check if a string starts with another, read input until a character is encountered, and execute commands on a binary analysis tool. Works with strings, input channels, and a context type representing an analysis session. Used to automate interaction with reverse engineering tools, extract data from binary files, and parse structured output.
